SIMPLE: warder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warder
<hw>Ward"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
wards or keeps; a keeper; a guard.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>warders</xex>
of the gate.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A truncheon or staff carried by a king or a
commander in chief, and used in signaling his will.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When, lo! the king suddenly changed his mind,⟦br⟧
Casts down his <qex>warder</qex> to arrest them there.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wafting his <qex>warder</qex> thrice about his head,⟦br⟧
He cast it up with his auspicious hand,⟦br⟧
Which was the signal, through the English spread,⟦br⟧
This they should charge.</q> <rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wardian</ent>⟦br⟧
